A TCP port is a logical communication endpoint used by the Transmission Control Protocol (TCP) to identify specific services or applications running on a device.

Think of it like this:

IP address = the buildingâ€™s street address

Port number = the specific apartment inside the building

When data is sent over the internet:

The IP address identifies the device.

The port number identifies the specific application or service on that device.

